                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Mi Aceh is a flavorful and spicy noodle dish originating from the Aceh province of Indonesia. 
                    This aromatic dish features thick yellow noodles simmered in a rich and spicy broth infused with a
                    blend of traditional Indonesian spices such as garlic, shallots, ginger, and turmeric. The broth is 
                    typically made with a combination of beef, seafood, or both, creating a hearty and satisfying meal. 
                    Often garnished with fresh herbs, such as cilantro and green onions, as well as lime wedges for a 
                    burst of citrus freshness, Mi Aceh tantalizes the taste buds with its bold flavors and comforting 
                    warmth, making it a beloved favorite among locals and food enthusiasts alike.
                </p>
